'''अ:कार''' name given to the nom. case n the Taittiriya Prātiśākhya. cf अ:कार ति प्रथमाविभक्तेरुपलक्षणम् T. Pr. I. 23.

'''अक् ( 1 )''' condensed expression प्रत्याहार ) representing the letters , इ, उ, ऋ and लृ in Pāṇini's rammar cf. P. VI.1.12, 101; II.4।2. (2) sign (विकरण) of the enedictive in Vedic Literature in he case of the root दृश् c. g. पितरं च ृशेयं P.III.l.86 V 2; ( 3 ) remn- nt of the termnination अकच् P. V. . 71 ; ( 4 ) substitute (अादेश) अकङ् or the last vowel of the word ुधातृ ( P.IV.1.97 ) e. g. सोघातकिः.

'''अक (1)''' affix अक substituted for the fiix वु given in Pāṇini's Grammar s ण्वुच् as in अाशिका,शायिका (P.III. .111); ण्वुल् as in कारकः, भोजको व्रजति, िचर्चिका (P.III.1.133, III.3. 0,108); वुच् as in उपकः (P.V.3.80); ुञ् as in निन्दकः, राजकम्, भालवकः (P. II.2.146, IV.2.39, 53 etc.); ुन् as in प्रवकः, सरकः; क्रमकः, पदकः. II.1.149, IV.2.6l etc.

