 he following rules lay down he different case affixes in the ense of the different Kārakas or uxiliaries of the verbal activity, rovided they are not shown or ndicated in any one of the above- entioned four ways; e. g. see the cc. case in कटं करोति, the inst, case n दात्रेण लुनाति, the dat. case in देवदत्ताय ां ददाति, the abl. case in ग्रामादा च्छति, or the loc.case in स्थाल्यां पचति.

