 ary). Regarding the case and con ugational afixes it can be said hat those affixes can, in a way: e looked upon as nitya or obliga- ory, as they have to be affixed to  crude nominal base or a root; here being a dictum that no crude ase without an affix can be used s also, no affix alone without a ase can be used. On the other and, the taddhita and kṛt affixes s also compounds are voluntary s, instead of them an independent ord or a phrase can be used to onvey the sense For a list of uch nitya affixes see M. Bh. on V. .7; (2) the word अनित्य is also sed in the sense of not-nitya, the ord नित्य being taken to mean ृताकृतप्रसङ्गि occurring before as well as fter another rule has been appli- d, the latter being looked upon as नित्य which does not do so. This
