 as fixed by Patañjali which, with  few additions made by the auth- rs of the Kāśika,as observed above, as traditionally come down to the resent day. The Aṣṭādhyāyī is elieved to be one of the six Ved- ṅga works which are committed to emory by the reciters of Ṛgveda. he text of the Aṣṭādhyāyī is recited ithout accents. The word अष्टाध्यायी as current in Patañjali's time; cf. िष्टज्ञानार्था अष्टाध्यायी M. Bh. on VI. .109.

'''अष्टाक्षरा''' a metre having eight sylla- les in a foot;cf.गायत्री सा चतुर्विंशत्यक्षरा । ष्टाक्षरास्त्रयः पादाः चत्वारो वा षडक्षराः R. r.XVI.9.

'''अष्टि''' name of a metre of four feet onsisting of 64 syllables in all, 12 yllables in the odd feet and 20 in he even feet; e. g. त्रिकदुकेषु महृिष: tc. R.V. II.22.1.

'''अस्''' (1) case affix of the nominative nd accusative plural and the ab- ative and genitive singular (जस् , स्, ङसि and ङस् ) (2) taddhita affix स् ( असि ) added to पूर्व, अधर and वर, by P.V.3.39: (3) compound- nding अस् ( असिच् ) applied to the ords प्रजा and मेधा standing at the nd of a Bahuvrīhi compound P.V.4.122): (4) Uṇādi affix अस् rescribed by the rule सर्वधातुभ्योऽसुन् nd subsequent rules (628-678) to orm words such as मनस्,सरस etc.(5) nding syllable अस्, with or with- ut sense, of words in connection ith which special operations are iven in grammar; cf. P.VI.4.14; f. also अनिनस्मन्ग्रहणान्यर्थवता चानर्थकेन च दन्तविधिं प्रयोजयन्ति Par.Śek. Pari. 16.

'''अस''' affix अस mentioned in the Niru- ta in the word अवस ( अव् + अस ) f. असो नामकरणः । तस्मान्नावगृह्णन्ति NirI.17.

'''असंख्य''' not possessing any notion of umber; the word is used in con-
 ection with avyayas or indeclina- les; यथैव हि अलिङ्गमव्ययमेवमसंख्यमपि . Bh. on II.4.82.

