'''असंज्ञा''' not used as a technical term or ame of a thing; cf. पूर्वपरावरदक्षिणोत्त- ापराधराणि व्यवस्थायामसंज्ञायाम् P.1.1.34.

'''असंनिकर्ष''' (।) separatedness as in the ase of two distinct words;(2) bsence of co-alescence preven- ing the sandhi; cf R.T. 68,70.

'''असंनिधान''' the same as असंनिकर्ष; see bove; e. g. भरा इन्द्र; तमु अभिप्रगायत.

'''असंप्रत्यय''' failure to understand the ense; cf. इतरथा ह्यसंप्रत्ययोऽकृत्रिमत्वाद्यथा ोके M. Bh. on I.1.23 Vārt. 3.

'''असंभव''' Impossibility of occurrence used in connection with an peration); cf नावश्यं द्विकार्ययोग एव िप्रतिषेधः । किं तर्हि । असंभवेपि । M. h. I.1.12 Vārt. 3; (2) impossibi- ity of a statement, mention, act tc. cf. असंभवः खल्वपि अर्थादेशनस्य M. h. on II.1.1.

'''असंयोग''' absence of the conjunction f consonants; cf. असंयोगाल्लिट् कित् .I.2.5.

'''असंहिता''' absence of juxta-position, bsence of connectedness; cf. दि तावत्संहितया निर्देशः क्रियते भ्वादय इति वितव्यम् । अथासंहितया भू अादय इति विंतव्यम्  M. Bh. on I.3.1.

'''असत्त्व'''(l) absence of सत्त्व or entity; 2) other than a substance i. e. roperty, attribute, etc. cf. प्रादयः सत्त्ववचना निपातसंज्ञा भवन्ति M. Bh. I. .59; cf. also सोऽसत्त्वप्रकृतिर्गणः M. h. on IV.1.44. cf. also चादयोऽ त्त्वे P.I.4.57.

'''असमर्थ''' (1) syntactically not con- ected, e. g. राज्ञः and पुरुषः in the entence भार्या राज्ञः पुरुषो देवदत्तस्य (2)


 nable to enter into a compound ord, the term is used in con- ection with a word which can- ot be compounded with another ord, although related in sense o it, and connected with it by pposition or by a suitable case ffix, the reason being that it is onnected more closely with an- ther word: cf. सापेक्षमसमर्थं भवति M. h. II.1.1.; e.g. the words कष्टं nd श्रितः in the sentence महत्हृ ष्टं श्रितः.

'''असमर्थसमास''' a compound of two ords, which ordinarily is in- dmissible, one of the two words eing more closely connected ith a third word, but which akes place on the authority of sage, there being no obstacle n the way of understanding the ense to be conveyed; e. g. देवदत्तस्य ुरुकुलम् । देवदत्तस्य दासभार्या । असूर्यंपश्यानि ुखानि, अश्राद्धभोजी ब्राह्मणः M. Bh. on I.1.1.

'''असमस्त''' not compounded, not en- ered into a compound with an- ther word; cf. समासे असमस्तस्य Hem. I.3.13.

