'''अाख्यात''' verbal form, verb; cf. ावप्रधानमाख्यातं सत्त्वप्रधानानि नामानि Nir. .1; चत्वारि पदजातानि नामाख्यातोपसर्गनि- ाताश्च M. Bh. I.1. Āhnika 1 ; also .Prāt. XII. 5, अाकार अाख्याते दादिश्च M. Bh. I.2.37 Vārt. 2, ख्यातमाख्यातेन क्रियासातत्ये Sid. Kau. n II.1.72, क्रियावाचकमाख्यातं V. r. V.1; cf. भारद्वाजकमाख्यातं भार्गवं नाम ाष्यते । भारद्वाजेन दृष्टत्वादाख्यातं भारद्वाज- ोत्रम् V. Prāt. VIII. 52; cf. also thar. Prāt.I.I.12, 18; 1.3.3,6; I.2.5 where ākhyāta means ver- al form. The word also meant in ncient days the root also,as differ- ntiated from a verb or a verbal orm as is shown by the lines तन्नाम ेनाभिदधाति सत्त्वं, तदाख्यातं येन भावं स धातुः .Pr.XII.5 where 'आख्यात' and
'धातु' are used as synonyms As the oot form such as कृ, भृ etc. as dis- inct from the verbal form, is never ound in actual use, it is immater- al whether the word means root or erb.In the passages quoted above rom the Nirukta and the Mahā- hāṣya referring to the four kinds f words, the word ākhyāta could e taken to mean root (धातु) or erb (क्रियापद). The ākhyāta or verb s chiefly concerned with the rocess of being and bccoming hile nouns (नामानि) have sattva or ssence, or static element as their eaning. Verbs and nouns are oncerned not merely with the acti- ities and things in this world but ith every process and entity; cf. ूर्वापूरीभूतं भावमाख्यातेनाचष्टे Nir.I.;अस्ति- वतिविद्यतीनामर्थः सत्ता । अनेककालस्थायि- ीति कालगतपौर्वापर्येण क्रमवतीति तस्याः क्रिया- ्वम् | Laghumañjūṣā. When a kṛt. ffix is added to a root, the static lement predominates and hence  word ending with a kṛt. affix in he sense of bhāva or verbal acti- ity is treated as a noun and regu-
 arly declined;cf.कृदभिहितो भावे द्रव्यवद् वति M.Bh. on II.2.19 and III. .67, where the words गति, व्रज्या, पाक nd others are given as instances. egarding indeclinable words end- ng with kṛt. affixes such as कर्तुं, ृत्वा, and others, the modern gram- arians hold that in their case the erbal activity is not shadowed y the static element and hence hey can be,in a way, looked upon s ākhyātas; cf. अव्ययकृतो भावे Vaiyā- araṇabhūṣaṇa.

