''आरडे''' KRISHNASHASTRI a re- uted Naiyāyika of Banaras of he nineteenth century, who rote, besides many treatises on yāya, a short gloss on the Stras f Pāṇini, called Pāṇini-sūtra-vṛtti.

'''अारि''' tad. affix applied to the word ूर्वतर when the whole word refers o a year, e.g.परारि in the last year; f. B.V.3.22 Vārt. 2.

'''आरु''' kṛt. affix applied to the roots शॄ nd वन्द् in the sense of habituated tc. e.g. शरारुः, वन्दारुः, cf P. III. .173.

'''अारोप''' attribution or imputation of roperties which leada to the econdary sense of a word; cf. प्रसिद्धश्च संज्ञादिरपि तद्गुणारोपादेव बुध्यते Par. ek. on Pari. 15.

'''अारोपर्णीय''' same as अभिनिधान: see above ाभनिधान.

'''अार्थ''' resultant from sense; made up f sense: अर्थस्य अयम् अार्थ: cf तदा- ितदन्तत्वमर्थसमाजग्रस्तम् Par. Śek. on ari.37.

'''आर्थसमाज''' combination of the mean- ngs (of the base and affix); see the ord अार्थ above.

''''आर्धधातुक''' a term used in contrast o the term सार्वधातुक for such ver- al and kṛt affixes, as are not ersonal endings of verbs nor


 arked with the mute letter श् f. तिङ्शित् सार्वधातुकम् । आर्धधातुकं ेषः। P.III.4.113 and 114. he personal endings of verbs in he perfect tense and the benedic- ive mood are termed ārdhadhā- uka, cf. P. III. 4.115, 116; while oth the terms are promiscuously ound utilised in the Vedic Litera- ure; cf. P. III. 4. 117. The main tility of the ārdhadhātuka term s the augment इ ( इट् ) to be refixed to the ārdhadhātuka ffixes. The term आर्धधातुका was n use in works of the old Vaiyā- araṇas; cf. अथवा आर्धधातुकासु इति क्ष्यामि कासु आर्धधातुकासु । उक्तिषु युक्तिषु ूढिषु प्रतीतिषु श्रुतिषु संज्ञासु M.Bh. on I. 4.35. It cannot be said how he term ārdhadhātuka originat- d. Probably such affixes or pra- yayas, like the kṛt affixes gene- ally, as could be placed after cer- ain roots only were called ārdha- hātuka, as contrasted with the erbal and the present participle ffixes which were termed sārva- hātuka on account of their eing found in use after every oot.

'''आर्धधातुका''' old term for आर्धधातुक; see र्धधातुक.

'''आर्धधातुकाधिकार''' the topic or section n Pāṇini's grammar where ope- ations, caused by the presence f an ārdhadhātuka affix ahead, are numerated, beginning with the ule आर्धधातुके VI.4.46 and ending ith न ल्यपि VI.4.69, Such opera- ions are summed up in the stanza तो लोपो चलोपश्च णिलोपश्च प्रयोजनम् । आल्लोप त्वमेत्वं च चिण्वद्भावश्च सीयुटि; M. Bh. as lso Kāś, on VI.4.46.

'''आर्ष''' derived from the holy sages; ounded on sacred tradition, such s the Vedāṅgas;cf. कृत्स्नं च वेदाड्गमनि-
 ्द्यमार्षम् R. Prāt. XIV 30. The word s explained as स्वयंपाठ by the com. n Vāj Prāt. IX.2I, and as Vaidika aṁdhi on X.l3. Patañjali has ooked upon the pada-pāṭha or ada-text of the Saṁhitās of the edas, as anārṣa, as contrasted ith the Saṁhitā text which is rṣa; cf. आर्ष्याम् in the sense संहितायाम् . Prāt. II.27; cf. also पदकारैर्नाम क्षणमनुवर्त्यम् M.Bh. on III.1.109.

'''आर्हीय''' tad-affixes ठक्, ठञ् etc. as also he senses in which the affixes are pplied, given in the section of āṇinis grammar P.V.1.19-71.

'''आल्''' case affix in Vedic literature .g. वनन्ता यजेत Kāś. on VII.1.39.

'''आलच्''' tad-affix (आल्) applied to the ord वाच् in the sense of 'talkative' .g. वाचालः; cf. P.V.2.124.

'''अालु''' tad. affix in the sense 'तन्न सह्यते' .g. शीतालुः, उष्णालुः P.V.2.122.

'''आलुच्''' kṛt. affix (आलु) applied to he roots स्पृह् गृह् पत् etc. cf. स्पृहयालुः. ृहयालुः, निद्रालुः etc. cf. P.III.2.158.

'''अावचन''' incomplete pronunciation, cf. षद् वचनम् M.Bh. on I.1.8.

'''आवत्''' tad-affix applied to the word म, cf. समाद् वसत M. Bh. on .4.30.

'''आवश्यक''' necessary notion or thing; f ओरावश्यके । आवश्यंभाव आवश्यकम् Kāś. n III.1.125, III.3.170.

'''आविष्टालिङ्ग''' having a fixed gen- er as opposed to अनाविष्ट्वि- ossessed of all genders; cf. अविश्- िङ्गा जातिः । यल्लिङमुपादाय प्रवर्तते न ल्लिङगे जहाति M. Bh. on I.2.52 .g. the word प्रमाण in प्रमाणं वेदाः.

'''अावृत्ति''' repetition, e.g. पदावृत्तिः; see om. on Vāj. Prāt. IV.21; cf. also वृत्तितः सप्तदशत्वं भवति M. Bh. I.1. hn. 2.

'''आशिस्''' the benedictive mood, cf. िदाशिषि P.III.4.104, called egularly as आशीर्लिङ्.



'''अशुबोध''' (1) name of a work on rammar written by Tārānātha alled Tarka-vācaspatī, a reput- d Sanskrit scholar of Bengal of he 19th century A.D. who ompiled the great Sanskrit ictionary named वाचस्पत्यकेाश and rote commentaries om many anskrit Shastraic and classical orks. The grammar called अाशुबोध s very useful for beginners; (2) ame of an elementary grammar n aphorisms written by रामकिंकर- रस्वती, which is based on the ugdhabodha of Bopadeva.

'''आश्रय''' (1) relation of dependence; f. अाश्रयात्सिद्धत्वं भविष्यति M. Bh. .1.12 Vārt. 4; (2) substratum, lace of residence; cf. गुणवचनानां ब्दानामाश्रयतो लिङ्गवचनानि भवन्ति । शुद्धं स्त्रम् । शुक्ला शाटी । शुक्लः कम्बलः । M. h. II.2.29.

'''आश्वलायनप्रातिशाख्य''' an authoritative rātiśākhya work attributed to aunaka the teacher of Āśvalāyana, elonging prominently to the Sak- la and the Bāṣkala Śakhās of the gveda. it is widely known by the ame Ṛk-Prātiśākhya. It is a etrical composition divided into . 8 chapters called Paṭalas, giving pecial directions for the proper ronunciation, recitation and pre- ervation of the Ṛksaṁhita by lay- ng down general rules on accents nd euphonic combinations and entioning phonetic and metrical eculiarities. It has got a masterly ommentary written by Uvvaṭa.

'''आसन्न''' nearest, most proximate: cf. िकारी यथासन्नम् V.Pr.I.142: cf. also he sūtra आसन्नः Śāk.I.1.7, explain- d as स्थानगुणप्रमाणादिभिर्यथास्वमासन्नः cf. lso अासन्नः Hem. VII.4.120.

'''अासत्ति''' close proximity of a word ith another; cf. णौ इत्यस्य आसत्तिवशात्
