'found or produced in', which is fixed to words तारका,पुष्पं, मुकुल and


 thers; e.g. तारकित, मुकुलित, सुखित, ुःखित etc.; cf. तदस्य संजातं तारकादिभ्य तच् P.V.2.36.

'''इतरेतर''' possessed of interdepende- ce; depending : upon each ther; cf. इतरेतरं कार्यमसद्वत् Candra ari. 5 }. Grammatical operations re of no avail if the rules stating hem are mutually depending n each other. The word इतरेतर as the sense of इतरेतराश्रय here.

'''इतरेतरयोग''' mutual relationship with ach other. Out of the four senses f the indeclinable च viz. समुच्चय, न्वाचय, इतरेतरयोग and समाहार, the vandva compound is formed of ords connected in the last two ays and not in the first two ays. The instances of द्वन्द्व in he sense of इतरेतरयोग are धवख- िरपलाशाः, प्लक्षन्यग्रोधौ etc; cf. Kāś.on . II.2.29 cf. also प्लक्षश्च न्यग्रोधश्चेत्युक्ते म्यत एतत्प्लक्षोपि न्यग्रोधसहायो न्यग्रोधेपि ्लक्षसहाय इति M.Bh. on II.2.29; cf. lso इतरेतरयोगः स यदा उद्रिक्तावयवभेदो वति Sīradeva Pari. 16.

'''इतरेतराश्रय''' depending upon each ther; cf. इतरेतराश्रयाणि च कार्याणि न ्रकल्पन्ते | तद्यथा | नौर्नावि बद्धा नेतरे- रत्राणाय भवति | M. Bh. on I.1.1.  ee इतरेतर above.

'''इत्कार्य''' a grammatical operation caus- d by इत् i. e. by a mute letter hich is purely indicatory; cf. एवं र्हि इत्कार्याभावादत्र इत्संज्ञा न भविष्यति M. h. I.3.2. See इत् above. त्व the substitution of short इ by ्याघ्वोरिच्च P.I.2.17, शास इदङ्हलोः P. I.4.3, etc.

'''इत्थंभूतलक्षण''' characterization; indi- ation by a mark: e. g. जटाभि- ्तापसः cf. इत्थंभूतलक्षणे च ( तृतीया ) P. I.3.21.

'''इत्नु''' kṛt affix mentioned by Pāṇini in I.4.55 as causing the substitution 
 f अय् for णि before it: e. g गदयित्नु:, ्तनयित्नु: M.Bh. on VI.4.55.

'''इत्र''' kṛt affix, added to the roots ऋ, ू, धू etc. in the sense of instru- ent cf. अर्तिलूधूसूखनसहचर इत्रः P.III. .184-6. e. g. अरित्रम् , लवित्रम् खनित्रम् tc. The words ending in इत्र have ot the acute accent on the last yllable; cf. P.VI.2.144.

'''इत्संज्ञक''' a letter which is termed इत्; ee इत् above.

'''इथुक्''' augment इथ् , e. g. यावतिथः, ताव- िथः cf. वतेरिथुक् P. V.2.53.

'''इदित्''' possessed of the mute indicatory etter इ; e. g the roots नदि, विदि nd the like, in whose case the ugment नुम् ( न् ) is affixed to the ast vowel; cf इदितो नुम् धातोः P. II.1.58.

'''इन''' ( 1 ) kṛt affix इ applied to the oots कृ, हृ, ग्रहृ, and भृ when they re preceded by certain words like ्तम्ब etc. in certain senses; e. g. ्तम्बकरिः, फलेग्रहिः, अात्मंभरिः; cf. P.III. .24-7;(2) kṛt affix इन् (णिनि) pres- ribed by P.III.3.170 e. g. अवश्यं- ारी, शतंदायी

'''इन''' ( l ) substitute for the inst. case nding in अा (टा) after bases ending n अ ; cf. टाङसिङसामिनात्स्याः P.VII.1. 2; (2) tad.aff इन affixed to पूर्वे e. . पथिभिः पूर्वेणैः cf. P. IV. 4. 133.

'''इनङ्'' substitute इन् for the last vowel f the words कल्याणी, सुभगा, दुर्भगा and thers before the affix ढ i. e. एय rescribed after these words in the ense of offspring e. g. काल्यााणिनेयः, ौभागिनेयः, कौलटिनेयः etc. cf.कल्याण्यादीना- िनङ् P. IV.I.126, 127.

'''इनच्''' tad. affix इन in the sense of poss- ssion applied to the word नि which s changed into चिक, e.g. चिकिनः cf. नच् पिटच् चिकचि च P.V.2.33.

'''इनि''' ( 1 ) kṛt affix इन् applied to the oots क्री with धि, जु with प्र, and the


 oots जि, दृ, क्षि and others, e. g. ोमविक्रयी, प्रजवी, जयी etc. cf. P.III .93 and III.2.156-157: (2) tad. ffix इन् affixed to the word पाण्डुकम्बल n the sense of 'covered with' ( cf. , IV.2.11), in the sense of collec- ion to the word खल e.g. खलिनी cf. .IV.2.51, to the word अनुब्राह्मण n sense 'student of' e.g. अनुब्राह्मणी f. P.IV.2.62, to the words कर्मन्द nd कृशाश्च cf. P.IV.3.lll, to the ord चूर्ण cf. P.IV.4.23 and to the ord श्राद्ध cf. P.V.2.85 and साक्षात् f. P. V. 2. 91 in specified senses nd in the general sense of posse- sion to words ending in अ, cf P. .2.115-117 and to certain other ords cf. P.V.2.128-37.

'''इनुण्''' kṛt affix इन्. by P. III.3.44 ollowed invariably by the tad. ffix अण् by P.V.4,15, e.g, सांरा- िणम् , सांकूटिनम्.

'''इन्दिरापति''' author of 'परीक्षा' a com- entary on the Paribhāṣendu- ekhara of Nāgeśabhaṭṭa.

'''इन्दुमित्र''' author of अनुन्यास, a com- entary on Nyāsa, the well-known ommentary on the Kāśikavṛtti by inendrabuddhi. Many quotations rom the Anunyāsa are found in he Paribhāṣāvṛtti of Sīradeva. he word इन्दु is often used for न्दुमित्र; cf. एतस्मिन् वाक्ये इन्दुमैत्रेययोः ाश्वतिकं विरोध: Sīra. Pari. 36.

'''इन्दुप्रकाश''' author of a commentary n the Paribhāṣenduśekhara.

'''इन्द्र''' name of a great grammarian who s believed to have written an ex- austive treatise on grammar efore Pāṇini; cf. the famous verse f Bopadeva at the commence- ent of his Dhātupāṭha इन्द्रश्चन्द्र: ाशकृत्स्नापिशली शाकटायनः । पाणिन्यमरजैनेन्द्रा यन्त्यष्टादिशाब्दिका: ॥ No work of ndra is available at present. e is nowhere quoted by
 āṇini. Many quotations believ- d to have been taken from his ork are found scattered in gram- ar works, from which it appears hat there was an ancient system revalent in the eastern part of ndia at the time of Pāṇini which ould be named ऐन्द्रव्याकरणपद्धति, o which Pāṇini possibly refers by he word प्राचाम्. From references,it ppears that the grammar was of he type of प्रक्रिया, discussing vari- us topics of grammar such as lphabet, coalescence, declension, ontext, compounds, derivatives rom nouns and roots, conjuga- ion, and changes in the base. he treatment was later on follow- d by Śākaṭāyana and writers of he Kātantra school.For details see ahābhāṣya ed. by D. E. Society, oona, Vol. VII pages 124-127.

'''इन्द्रदत्त''' author of the * Gūḍhaphakki- āprakāśa', a gloss on the difficult assages in the Mahābhāṣya.

'''ईप्''' a technical term for द्वितीया (accu- ative case ) in the Jainendra rammar; cf. कर्मणीप् Jain. 1.4.2. प् a technical term in the Jainen- ra Vyākaraṇa  for सप्तमी (the loca- ive case).

'''इफ''' tad. affix applied to र ( letter र् ) n the sense of the consonant र्; e. . रेफःल; cf. रादिफः P.III.3.108 ārt. 4.

'''इम''' augment इ added to the base तृणह, fter the last vowel, e. g. तृणोढि; cf. ृणह इम् P.VII.3.92.

'''इमन्''' or इमनिच् tad. affix इमन् applied o the words पृथु, मृदु, महत्, लघु, गुरु, ords showing colour and words uch as दृढ, परिवृढ, भृश, शीत, उष्ण etc. n the sense of 'quality' or 'attri- ute': cf Pāṇ. V. 1.122, 123. For hanges in the base before the affix इमन् see P. VI.4.154-163.



'''इमप्''' kṛt. affix इम applied to words howing भाव or verbal activity; .g. पाकिमम्, त्यागिमम्;cf. भावप्रत्ययान्तादि- ब्वक्तव्यः Kāś. on P.IV.4.20.

'''इय''' tad affix ( घन् ) in the sense of
'pity'; e. g. देवियः, यज्ञियः; cf. P.IV. .79.

'''इयङ्'' substitute for the last इ efore a vowel generally in the ase of monosyllabic roots end- ng in इ and the word स्त्री; .g. चिक्षियुः, नियौ नियः, स्त्रियौ स्त्रियः; f. अचि क्षुधातुभ्रुवां य्वोरियङुवङौ P.VI. .77-80.

'''इया''' case-ending for inst. sing. in edic Literature; e. g. उर्विया, ार्विया; cf. P.VII.1.39. and Vārt.1 here on.

'''इर्''' mute indicatory ending of roots, ! ignifying the application of the  orist sign अ(अङ्) optionally;e g. भिदत् or अभैत्सीत् from the root  िद् (भिदिर् in Dhātupāṭha) cf. lso अच्छिदत्,अच्छैत्सीत् from छिद्(छिदिर्); f. P.III.1.57.

'''इरच्''' tad. affix ( इर् ) in the sense of ossession applied in Vedic Lite- ature to रथ e.g. रथिरः; cf. P.V. .109 Vārt.3.

'''इरन''' tad. affix ( इर ) in the sense of ossession applied in Vedic Lite- ature; to मेघा e.g. cf. P. मधिरः .2.109 Vārt. 3.

'''इरित''' a root ending with mute indi- atary ending इर्. See इर्.

'''इरे''' ( इरेच् ) substitute for the perfect rd pers ， pl. Ātm. affix झ; e.g. क्रिरे, ऊचिरे etc.; cf. P.III.4.81.

'''इल''' tad. affix applied to the words ाश, अश्वत्थ, पलाश and others in the our senses prescribed in P.IV. .67-70; e.g. काशिलः, अश्वत्थिल:, लाशिलः cf.P.IV.2.80.

'''इलच्''' (I) tad. affix इल (इलच्) in the ense of pity; e. g. देवियः, यज्ञिलः cf.
 .IV.2.79. The tad.affix घन् is also ffixed in the same sense. See ईय. 2) tad. affix इल (इलच्) in the sense f possession, prescribed after the ords फेन, लोमन् कपि, सिकता, शर्करा, ुन्द, उदर्, घट, यव etc.; e.g. फेनिल, ोमिल, कपिल, सिकतिल तुन्दिल etc. cf. .V.2.99, 100, 105, 117.

'''इश्''' substitute for इदम् before an ffix called 'vibhakti': e. g. इह; cf: .V.3.3.

'''इष्ट''' a word frequently used in he Vārttikas and the Mahābh- ṣya and other treatises in the enses of (1) a desired object, 2) a desired purpose, (3) a esired statement, (4) a desired orm i.e. the correct form : cf. ष्टान्वाख्यानं खल्वपि भवति M. Bh.I.1. hn. 1. योगविभागादिष्टसिद्धिः Pari.Śek. ari. 114.

'''इष्टतन्त्रव्याकरण''' a short treatise on rammar ascribed to Jayadeva.

'''इष्टादि''' a class of words headed by he word इष्ट to which the taddhita ffix इन् ( इनि ) is added in the ense of अनेन i. e. 'by him' i. e. y the agent of the activity de- oted by the past pass. participles ष्ट and others; cf. इष्टी, यज्ञे, पूर्ती श्राद्धे tc. Kāś, on P.V.2.88.

'''इष्टि''' a word generally used in the statements made in the Mahā hāṣya, similar to those of the ūtrakāra and the Vārttikakāras, hich are 'desired ones' with a iew to arrive at the correct orms of words; cf. प्राप्तिज्ञो देवानां- ्रियो न त्विाष्टिङ,	इष्यत एतद् रूपमिति . Bh. on II. 4.56.

'''इष्ठ''' the superlative tad. affix इष्ठन् in he sense of अतिशायन or अतिशय  excellence ). The commentators, owever, say that the taddhita ffixes तम and इष्ठ,like all the tadd- ita affixes showing case-relations,


 re applied without any specific ense of themselves, the affixes howing the sense of the base itself  स्वार्थे ): e. g गुरुतमः, गरिष्ठः पटुतमः, ठिष्ठः पचतितमाम्, कर्तृतमः, करिष्ठः etc. cf. .V.3.55-64 The affixes ईयस् and ष्ठ are applied only to such subst- ntives which denote quality; cf. .V.3.58.

'''इष्ठन्''' the same as इष्ठ. See इष्ठ.

'''इष्ठवद्भाव''' possession of the same pro- erties for causing grammatical perations as the tad. affix इष्ठन् ossesses, as for instance, the elision f the syllable beginning with the ast vowel ( टिलोप ), substitution of he masc. base for the fem. base पुंवद्भाव) etc., before the denom affix णिच्; e.g. एतयति in the sense f एनीं आचष्टे; similarly प्रथयति, पटयति, वयति, cf. M.Bh. on. P.VI.4. 55 Vārt, 1.

'''इष्णु''' kṛt affix इष्णुच् applied,in the sense f 'possessed of habitual behavi- ur action, or splendid accomp- ishment,' to the roots अलंकृ, निराकृ, ्रजन् , उत्पत् etc. e.g अलंकरिष्णुः,उत्पतिष्णुः, हिष्णुः,चरिष्णुः etc.;cf.P.III.2.136-138.

'''इष्यै''' kṛt affix in Vedic Literature in the ense of the infinitive, e. g. रेहिष्यै, व्यथिष्यै; cf P.III.4.10.

'''इस्''' ( l ) substitute इस् for the vowel f the roots, मी, मा, दा, धा, रभ्, पत् etc. efore the desiderative aifix सन्; .g. मित्सति, दित्सति, अारिप्सते etc. cf.P. II.4.54; (2) uṅādi affix इस् e.g. र्पिस्.

'''इस्नुच्''' alternative affix mentioned in he Mahābhāṣya in the place of ष्णुच् ; cf M. Bh.on III. 2.57. See ष्णुच् .



'''ई''' the long vowel ई which is techni- ally included n the vowel
  in Pāṇini's alphabet being he long tone of that vowel; (2) ubstitute ई for the vowel अा of he roots घ्ना and ध्मा before the requentative sign यङ् as for ex- mple in जेघ्रीयते, देध्मीयते, cf. P.VII. .31; (3) substitute ई for the owel अ before the affixes वि and ्यच् as, for instance, in शुक्लीभवति, ुत्रीयति etc.; cf.P.VII.4.32, 33; 4) substitute ई for the vowel अा t the end of reduplicated bases s also for the vowel आ of bases nding in the conjugational sign ा, e.g. मिमीध्वे, लुनीतः etc.; cf P.VI. .113; (5) substitute ई for the oc. case affix इ ( ङि ) in Vedic iterature, e.g. सरसी for सरसि in दृतिं  शुश्कं सरसी शयानम्,: cf. Kāś. on P. II.1.39: (6) tad. affix ई in the ense of possession in Vedic Litera- ure as for instance in रथीः,सुमङ्गलीः, f. Kāś on. P.V.2.109: (7) the em. affix ई ( ङीप् , ङीञ् or ङीन् ); cf. .IV.1.58, 15-39, IV.1.40-65, V.1.13.

'''ईक''' tad. affix ईकक added to शक्ति nd यष्टि e.g. शाक्तकिः fem. शाक्तीकी; ाष्टीकः; cf. P.IV.4.59; (2) tad. affix क added to कर्क and लोहित in the ense of comparison, e. g. कार्कीकः, ौहितीकः ( स्फटिकः ), cf. Kāś. on P.V. .110; (3) tad. affix ईकक् added to हिस् e.g. बाहीकः cf. बहिषष्टिलोपो यश्च, कक्च P.IV.1.85. Vārt. 4-5; (4) tad ffix इकङ् in Vedic Literature added o बहिस् e.g. बाहीकः cf. Kāś.on P. IV. .85,Vārt.6; (5) tad. affix ईकन् addcd o खारी e.g. द्विखारिकम्; cf. P. V. .33.

'''ईट्''' augment ई prefixed to a Sārvad- ātuka (strong) affix beginning ith a consonant after the roots ्रू, रु, स्तु, and others e.g. अब्रवीत्, ोरवीति, स्तवीति, अकार्षीत्, अर्वादीत् etc.; f. P. VII. 3.93-98.



'''ईत्''' long vowel ई as different from  or ई३ prescribed as a substitute; f. P.VI.3.27, VI.3.97.

'''ईदित्''' (a root) possessed of long ई as  mute indicatory ending meant  for prohibiting the addition of the ugment इ to the past part. ter-|. inations त and तवत् ; e.g. लग्नः, ीप्तः etc.; cf. P VII.2.14.

'''ईप्सित''' a desired object, which, in con- ection with transitive roots, gets he designation कर्म,when the agent as a keen desire for it; cf. कर्तुरी- ्सिततमं कर्म P.I.4.49.

'''ईमसच्''' tad. affix ईमस added to the ord मल in sense of possession: . g. मलीमस:, cf. P. V. 2.114.

'''ईय''' substitute for the tad.afix छ; e.g: ालीयः, मालीयः etc; cf P. VII. 1.2 nd IV. 2, 114.

'''ईयङ्'''' afix ईय added to the root ऋत्, ् showing the application of the tmanepada affixes; e. g. ऋतीयते f. P. III.1.29

'''ईयस्''' tad-affix ईयसुन् , showing superi- rity or excellence of one indivi- ual over another in respect of a uality, added to a substantive ex- resive of quality; when the subst- ntive ends in the affix तृ, that aHix ृ is removed: e.g. पटीयान्, लघीयान, रीयान्, देहीयसी (धेनुः) cf.P.V.3.57-64.

'''ईयसुन्''' the same as ईयस् which see bove.

'''ईरच्''' tad-affix added to the word अण्ड n the sense of possession: e.g. ण्रडीरः;cf. काण्डाण्डादीरन्नीरचौ P.V.2.111.

'''ईश्''' substitute ई for इदम् before the ad-affixes दृक्, दृश् and वतु; e.g. ईदृक् दृश् also ईदृक्षः; cf. P.VI.3.90.

'''ईश्वरकान्त''' author of 'Dhātumāla', a hort metrical treatise on roots.

'''ईश्वरानन्द्''' author of (l) a gloss on aiyaṭa's Mahābhāṣya-pradīpa,
 nd (2)an independent treatise Śābdabodhataraṅgiṇī. He is believed to ave been a pupil of सत्यानन्द and ived in the latter part of the 16th entury A.D.

'''ईषच्छ्वास''' an external effort ( बाह्य-प्रयत्न) n the production of sound charac- orized by the emission of breath, hen the cavity made by the cords f the throat is kept wide apart, s found in the utterance of the onsonants श्, ष् and स.

