'''एकमुनिपक्ष''' a view or doctrine pro- ounded by one of the many ncient sages or munis who are elieved to be the founders of  Sastra; a view propounded nly by Pāṇini, to the exclusion f Kātyāyana and Patañjali; f. एकमुनिपक्षे तु अचो ञ्णितीत्यत्राच इति ोगं विभज्य...व्यवस्थितविभाषात्रोक्ता Dur- haṭa-Vṛtti I.1.5; see also I.4.24, I.3.18. 2

'''एकयोग''' (1) combination of two Sutras nto one:cf.अथवा एकयोगः करिष्यते वृद्धिरादै- देड्गुण इति M.Bh.P.I.1.3,I.4.59,V.2. 5; (2) one and the same Sūtra;cf. कयेागनिर्दिष्टानां सह वा प्रवृत्ः:सह बा निवृत्तिः ari.Śek.Pari.17; cf.also एकयोगानिर्दि- ्टानामप्येकदेशानुवृत्तिर्भवति P. IV.1.27, ārt. 2, Pari. Śek. Pari. 39.

'''एकयोगलक्षण''' characterized by i.e. entioned in one and the same ule: cf. एकयोगगलक्षण तुग्दीर्घत्वे M.Bh. n P. I. 1. 62. Vart. 10. See also . Bh.on P. VI.1.37.

'''एकवचन''' singular number; affix of he singular numberin Pāṇini's gra- mar applied to noun-bases ( प्राति- दिक) and roots when the sense of he singular number is to be conw- yed; the singular sense can be of he form of an individual or colle- tion or genus. The word एकवचन n the technical sense of singular umber is found used in the rātiśākhyas and Nirukta also.

'''एकवत्त्व''' or '''एकवद्भाव''' use or treatment f the plural sense as if it is singu- ar: cf. एकवद्भावीsनर्थक: 1 समाहृारैकत्वात् .Bh. on II. 4.12. Vart. 5.

'''एकवर्ण'''(a pada) made up of a single etter; _ cf. एकवर्ण पदम् आ, उ इति: ommentary on R.Pr. K.2; cf. lso V.Pr.IV. 144-145 where एकवर्ण s defined as एकप्रयत्ननिर्वर्त्य capable f being produced with a single ffort. Pāṇini gives the term अपृक्त o an affix made up of one single etter; cf.अपृक्त एकाल् प्रत्यय: P.I.2.41.

'''एकवाक्य''' an expression giving ome dea, either asingle or a composite ne. A positive statement and its egation, so also, a general rule nd its exception are looked upon s making a single sentence on ccount of their mutual expectancy ven though they be sometimes etached from each other cf. 

 िदेशस्थमपि सदेकवाक्यं भवति M. Bh. on II.4.67; cf. also निषेधवाक्यानामपि िषेध्यविशेषाकाङ्क्षत्वाद्विध्येकवाक्यतयैव अन्वयः । त्रैकवाक्यता पर्युदासन्यायेन । संज्ञा शास्त्रस्य तु ार्यकालपक्षे न पृथग्वाक्यार्थबोधः Par. Śek n Pari. 3. Such sentences are, in act, two sentences, but, to avoid he fault of गौरव, caused by वाक्यभेद, rammarians hold them to be omposite single sentences.

'''एकविभक्ति''' a pada having the same ase in the various dissolutions of he compound word: e. g. the ord कौशाम्बी in the compound ord निष्कौशाम्बिः, which stands only n the ablative case कौशाम्ब्याः, alth- ugh the word निष्क्रान्त, which stands or the word निस्, could be used in any cases. The word नियतविभक्तिक s also used in the same sense.

'''एकवृत्ति''' single vṛtti or gloss on the edic as well as classical portions f grammar. Puruṣottamadeva has sed this term in his Bhaāṣāvṛtti o contrast his Vṛtti (भाषावृत्ति) with he Kāśikāvṛtti and the Bhāgavṛtti hich deal with both the portions; f.अनार्ष इत्येकवृत्तावुपयुक्तम् Bhāṣāvṛtti on .1.16, cf.also Bhāṣāvṛtti on III. .99, IV.3.22 and VI.3.20.एकवृत्ति s possibly used by Puruṣottama- eva in the sense of मुख्यवृत्ति or साधा- णवृत्ति i. e. the common chief gloss n both the portions.

'''एकशब्द''' a word having one sense nly, as opposed to अनेकशब्द many ords having the same sense or ynonyms which are given in निघण्टुः s also in अमरकोषः; cf. अथ यान्यनेकार्थनि कशब्दानि तान्यतेनुक्रमिष्यामः Nir. IV.1.

'''एकशेष''' a kind of composite formation n which only one of the two or ore words compounded together ubsists, the others being elided; f. एकः शिष्यते इतरे निवर्तन्ते वृक्षश्च वृक्षश्च ृक्षौ ।  Kāśikā on सरूपाणामेकशेष एक- 
 िभक्तौ P.I.2.64; cf. also सुरूपसमुदा- ाद्दि विभक्तिर्या विधीयते । एकस्तत्रार्थवान् सिद्धः मुदायस्य वाचकः । Bhāṣāvṛtti on P. I. .64. There is a dictum of gra- marians that every individual bject requires a separate ex- ression to convey its presence. ence, when there is a dual sense, he word has to be repeated, as lso the word has to be multiplied hen there is a plural sense. In urrent spoken language, however, n such cases the word is used nly once. To justify this ingle utterance for conveying the ense of plurality, Pāṇini has laid own a general rule सरूपाणामेकशेष कविभक्तौ and many other similar ules to cover cases of plurality not f one and the same object, but lurality cased by many objects, uch as plurality caused by ideas oing in pairs or relations such s parents, brothers and sisters, rand-father and grand-son, male nd female. For example, see the ords वृक्षश्च वृक्षश्च वृक्षौ; Similarly वृक्षाः or many trees, पितरौ for माता च िता च; देवौ for देवी च देवश्च: cf. also he words श्वशूरौ, भ्रातरौ, गार्ग्यौ (for गार्ग्य nd गार्ग्यायण),आवाम् (for त्वं च अहं च), यौ for स च यश्च) and गावः fem. अजा fem. श्वाः masc. irrespective of the indi- iduals being some males and ome females. Pāṇini has devoted 0 Sūtras to this topic of Eka- eṣa. The Daiva grammar has ompletely ignored this topic. atanjali has very critically and xhaustively discussed this topic. ome critics hold that the topic f एकशेघ did not exist in the ori- inal Aṣṭādhyāyī of Pāṇini but it as interpolated later on, and ad- uce the long discussion in the ahābhāṣya especially the Pūrva- akṣa therein, in support of their


 rgument. Whatever the case be, he Vārttikakāra has commented pon it at length; hence, the ddition must have been made mmediately after Pāṇini, if at all here was any. For details see ahābhāṣya on I.1.64 to 73 as al- o,Introduction p. 166-167, Vol.7 f the Mahābhāṣya published by he D. E. Society, Poona.

'''एकशेषनिर्देश''' statement by subsistence of ne word out of many. The phrase s very often used in the Mahā- hāṣya where the omission of an ndividual thing is explained by aying that the expression used is  composite one including the mitted thing along with the thing lready expressed; cf. एकशेषनिर्देशो- म् | सर्वादीनि च सर्वादीनि च सर्वादीनि ! . Bh. on I.I.27, on I.1.59, .2.39, as also on I.3.1 Vārt. 5,I.4. 0l Vārt. 3, II.1.1. Vārt. 19 etc.

'''एकश्रुति''' that which has got the same ccent or tone; utterance in the ame tone; monotone. The word s applied to the utterance of the ocative noun or phrase calling a an from a distance, as also to hat of the vowels or syllables ollowing a Svarita vowel in the aṁhitā i.e. the continuous utter- nce of Vedic sentences; cf. एकश्रुति ूरात्संबुद्वौ and the foll. P.I.2.33-40 nd the Mahābhāṣya thereon. In is discussion on I.2.33 Patañjali as given three alternative views bout the accent of Ekaśruti sylla- les : (a) they possess an ac- ent between the उदात्त (acute) nd अनुदात्त (grave), (b) they are ; n the same accent as is posses- ed by the preceding vowel, (c) kaśruti is looked upon as the eventh of the seven accents; f. सैषा ज्ञापकाभ्यामुदात्तानुदात्तयोर्मध्यमेकश्रुति- न्तरालं ह्रियते। ... सप्त स्वरा भवन्ति | उदात्त:,
 दात्ततर:, अनुदात्तः, अनुदात्ततर:, स्वरितः ्वरिते य उदात्त: सोन्येन विशिष्टः, एकश्रुतिः प्तमः । M.Bh. on P.I.2.33.

'''एकस्वर''' possessed of one vowel,mono- yllabic; a term used by Hema- andra in his grammar for the erm एकाच् of Pāṇini: cf. आद्योंश कस्वरे Hem.IV.1.2, which means he same as एकाचेा द्वे प्रथमस्य P.VI.1.1.

'''एकहलादि''' having a single consonant t the beginning: _ cf एकहलादौ ूरयितव्येSन्यतरस्याम् P.VI.3.59.

'''एकहल्मध्य''' (a vowel) placed between wo single consonants; e.g the owel अ in पच्, रम्, रण्, etc.

'''एकाक्षर''' consisting of one single sylla- le ; e.g. स्व, भू, वाच् etc. cf. एकाक्षरा- ्कृते जातेः सप्तम्यां च न तौ स्मृतौ M.Bh. n P.V.2.115, as also on VI.1.168, I.4.161.

'''एकाच्''' possessed of a single vowel, onosyllabic: cf. एकाचौ द्वे प्रथमस्य P. I.1.1.

'''एकाच्पाद''' name given by Sīradeva nd other grammarians to the irst pāda of the sixth adhyāya cf āṇini's Aṣṭādhyāyī, as it begins ith the sūtra एकाचो द्वे प्रथमस्य I.1.1.

'''एकादेश''' a single substitute in the place f two original units; e.g. ए in the lace of अ and इ,or ओ in the place f अ and उ. The ādeśas or substitu- es named पूर्वरूप and पररूप arelooked pon as ekadeśas in Pāṇini's rammar although instead of hem, the omission of the latter nd former vowels respectively, is rescribed in some Prātiśākhya orks. गुण and वृद्धि are sometimes ingle substitutes for single origi- als, while they are sometimes kadeśas for two original vowels .g. तवेदम्, ब्रह्मौदनः, उपैति, प्रार्च्छति, गाम्, ीमन्तः etc.; see P.VI.1.87 to ll l, f. also A.Pr.II 3.6.




'''एकादेशस्वर''' an accent prescribed for  he single substitute,as, for instance, y rules like उदात्तस्वरितयोर्यणः स्वरितो- ुदात्तस्य and the following rules P. I.2.4, 5 and 6.

'''एकान्त''' part, portion. Augments or gamas in the Vyākaraṇa Śāstra re looked upon as forming a part f the word to which they are ; ttached; cf. अथ यस्यानुबन्ध आसज्यते, िं स तस्य एकान्तो भवति आहोस्विदनेकान्तः ; कान्तस्तत्रेापलब्धेः | M. Bh. on I.3.9, ārt.9; cf. also एकान्ताः Par. Śek. ari, 5.

'''एकान्तर''' separated or intervened by ne single thing, a letter or a | ord; e. g. अां पचसि देवदत्त, where ेवदत्त follows अाम् with one word चसि intervening: cf. आम एकान्तरमाम- ्त्रितमनन्तिके P.VIII.1.55.

'''एकार''' the letter ए: looked upon as a iphthong ( संध्यक्षर ) made up of he letters अ and इ. The combina- ion of the two constituent parts s so complete as cannot allow any f the two parts to be indepen- ently working for saṁdhi or any ther operation with its adjoining  etter: cf नाव्यपवृत्तस्य अवयवे तद्विधिर्यथा ्रव्येषु M. Bh. Śivasūtra 3 Vārt. 9.

'''एकार्थ''' (1) possessed of one sense as ontrasted with बह्वर्थ, द्व्यर्थ etc: (2) ynonym, cf. बहवो हि शब्दा एकार्था वन्ति | तद्यथा इन्द्रः शक्रः पुरुहूतः पुरंदरः । . Bh. on I.2.45 Vārt. 9: (3) ossessed of a composite sense; f. समासे पुनरेकार्थानि M. Bh. on II. .l Vārt I. The words एकार्थ्य nd एकार्थत्व derived from the word कार्थ are often found used in the ense of 'possession of a compo- ite sense' एकार्थस्य भाव: एकार्थता,एकार्थ्यं कार्थत्वं वा; cf. समासस्यैकार्थत्वंत्सिंज्ञाया प्रसिद्धिः M. Bh. on P.I.2.42 ārt 1; cf. also the word एकार्थी- ावः (4) potent to be connected;
 मर्थ; cf. सुप्सुपा एकार्थम् ( समस्यते ) C. y. II.2.1; (5) analogous समाना- िकरण cf. एकार्थं चानेकं च । एकः समानः र्थ: अधिकरणं यस्य तदेकार्थं समानाधिकरणम् em. Vy. III. 1.22: cf. also एकार्थे  | Śāk. II.1.4.

'''एकार्थीमाव''' union of meanings; one f the two ways in which the ord सामर्थ्य is explained; cf. एकार्थी- ावो वा सामर्थ्यं स्याद् व्यपेक्षा वा | M. Bh. n II.1.1.

'''एकाल्''' possessed of one single pho- etic element or letter cf. अपृक्त काल् प्रत्ययः P. I.2.41.

'''एकीभाव''' fusion, mixture, union, com- ination (of 2 or more letters); cf. दात्तवति एकीभावे उदात्तं सन्ध्यमक्षरम्, R. r.III.6.एकीभाव is said to be result- ng from the coalescence called भिनिहितसन्धि, cf. R. Pr. II.16, 17.

'''एगेलिंग्''' ( Eggeling ) a well-known erman scholar of Sanskrit rammar who flourished in the 9th century and who edited he Kātantra Vyākaraṇa with the ommentary of Durgasiṁha and any appendices in 1876.

'''एङ्''' a brief term ( प्रत्याहार ) for the wo diphthong letters ए and ओ; f. एङ्ह्रस्वात्संबुद्धेः P.VI.1.69, एङः दान्तादति VI.1.109. etc.

'''एच्''' a short term (प्रत्याहार) in Pāṇini's rammar standing for diphthongs r letters ए,ए,ओ, औ, e.g. एचोयवायावः .VI.1.78, एच इग् ह्रस्वादेशे P.I.1.48.

'''एजटेन्''' [Edgerton, Dr. Franklin] an merican Sanskrit scholar and uthor of Buddhist Hybrid Sans- rit Grammar and Dictionary.'

'''एणीकृत''' A fault in pronunciation hen the voice is indistinct, and he word pronounced is not dis- inctly heard; cf. एणीकृतः अविशिष्टः । िमयमोकारः अथौकार इति यत्र संदेहः Pradīpa n M.Bh.I.1.1,explained as अवशिष्ट: ंश्लिष्टः संदिग्ध इति यावत् by Nāgeśa in


 is Uddyota.

'''एण्य''' tad. affix एण्य applied to the ord प्रावृष् in the general शैषिक enses; cf. प्रावृष एण्यः । प्रावृषेण्यः बलाहकः āś. on P.IV.3.17.

'''एत्''' the vowel ए; cf. ईदूदेद्द्विवचनं प्रगृह्यम् .I.1.11.

'''एतावत्त्व''' limitation of the kind; 'such nd such' (words etc.); cf. A. Pr.I.

'''एत्व''' the substitution of ए; cf. बहुवचने ल्येत् (P. VII.3.103) इति एत्वं प्राप्नोति .Bh. on P.V.3.10.

'''एत्य''' tad. affix applied to the in- eclinable दूर; e. g. दूरेत्यः पथिकः । cf. ूरादेत्यः दूरेत्य: Kāś.on P.IV.2.104: cf. lso दूरादेत्यो वक्तव्यः । दूरेत्य: M.Bh. on .IV.2.104.

'''एदित्''' marked by the mute indicatory etter ए. Roots marked with indi- atory ए do not allow वृद्धि for heir vowel in the aorist: e.g. रगीत्, अलगीत्; cf. P.VII.2.5.

'''एद्यवि''' tad. affix एद्यवि applied to the ronoun पर when the word refers o a day;cf. परस्स्मिन्नहनि परेद्यवि Kāś. on .V.3.22.

'''प्रद्युसच्''' tad. affix एद्युस् applied to the ronouns पूर्व, अन्य, अन्यतर, इतर, पर, अधर, उभय and उत्तर when the ords so formed refer to a day; . g. पूर्वेद्युः, अन्येद्युः etc.: cf. P.V.3.22.

'''एधाच्''' tad.affix एधा substituted for the ad. affix धा optionally,when appli- d to the words द्वि and त्रि. e.g.द्विधा, ्वेधा, दैधम्, त्रिधा, त्रेधा, त्रैधम्; cf. Kāś. on धाच्च P.V.3.46.

'''एनप्''' tad. affix एन applied to उत्तर, अधर, nd दक्षिण optionally instead of the ad. affix आति in the senses of दिक्, ेश and काल, e.g. उत्तरेण, उत्तरतः उत्तरात्, ords with this एन at the end overn the acc. case of the word yntactically connected with them. . g. तत्रागारं धनपतिगूहान् उत्तरेण Kālidāsa: eghadūta;cf.एनपा द्वितीया P.II.3.31.

'''एप्''' a term used in the Jainendra yākaraṇa for the term गुण of āṇini standing for the vowels , ए and ओ; cf. ऋतः समादेरेप् Jain. y. V.2.122.

'''एफ''' ending added to the consonant र hen a mention of it is to be ade; cf. T.Pr.I.19: e.g. रेफ.

'''एलिम''' (1) kṛt. afix केलिमर् e.g. पचेलिमा ाषा cf. P. III.1.96 Vārt. 1: (2) ṇādi affix एलिमच् applied to पच् f. पच एलिमच् Uṇ. S.IV.37.

'''एलु''' tad-affix चेलु in the sense of unable o bear, found in Vedic Literature nly; e.g. हिमेलुः cf. हिमाक्चेलुर्वक्तव्यः | .V.2.122 Vārt. 7.

'''एव''' (l) a particle in the sense of re- ulation (नियम) ; cf. एवकारः किमर्थः ियमार्थ: M. Bh. on V.3.58: (2) . eterminant indeclinable: cf. एव त्यवधारणे; cf. इष्टतोवधारणार्थस्तर्हि । यथैवं िज्ञायेत । अजादी गुणवचनादेवेति M. Bh. n V.3.58.

'''एवकारकरण''' use of the word एव; cf. क्तममैवाव्ययेन इत्यत्र एवकारकरणस्य प्रयो- नम्० M.Bh. on P.III.4.24.

