'karman' as are connected with a erbal activity and used in the ccusative case; cf. कर्तुरीप्सिततमं र्म; तथायुक्तं चानीप्सितम् ;  अकथितं च and तिबुद्धिप्रत्यवसानार्थशब्दकर्माकर्मकाणामणि कर्ता णौ P.I.4.49-52;cf also यत् क्रियते तत् र्म Kāt. II.4.13, कर्त्राप्यम् Jain I. 2. 20 and कर्तुर्व्याप्यं कर्म Hem. II. 2. 3. ometimes a kāraka, related to he activity ( क्रिया) as saṁpradāna, pādāna or adhikaraṇa is also treat- d as karma, if it is not meant or esired as apādāna,saṁpradāna etc. t is termed अकथितकर्म in such cases; f. अपादानादिविशेषकथाभिरविवरक्षितमकथितम् āś. on I.4.51. See the word कथित above. Karman or object s to be achieved by an activity or ्रिया; it is always syntactically con- ected with a verb or a verbal deri- ative.When connected with verbs r verbal derivatives indeclinabl- s or words ending with the affixes क, क्त, क्तवतु, तृन् , etc, it is put in he accusative case. It is put in he genitive case when it is con- ected with affixes other than those entioned above; cf. P, II.3.65, 9. When, however, the karman s expressed ( अभिहित ) by a verbal ermination ( तिङ् ), or a verbal oun termination (कृत्), or a noun- ffix ( तद्धित ), or a compound, it is ut in the nominative case. e.g. टः क्रियते, कट: कृतः, शत्यः, प्राप्तोदकः ग्रामः tc. It is called अभिहित in such ases;cf. P.II.3.1.Sec the word अन- िहित above.The object or Karman hich is ईप्सिततम is described to be f three kinds with reference to he way in which it is obtained

